      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 71: 🟡 The threshold `0.001` for detecting an aspect-ratio change is a magic number. For typical video resolutions (e.g., 1920×1080 → invAspect ≈ 0.5625), a difference of 0.001 is ~0.18%, which seems reasonable — but for very wide aspect ratios (e.g., 21:9 → invAspect ≈ 0.4286), the same absolute threshold is proportionally larger. Consider using a relative comparison or documenting why the absolute threshold is acceptable:\n\n```suggestion\n        if (_lastInvAspect \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 Math.abs(r - _lastInvAspect) / _lastInvAspect \u003e 0.01) {\n```",
      "revId": "b2c75e980a9cda3bc84af68e32b4c9299b4409d7",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
