      "writtenOn": "2026-05-18T01:51:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 75: 🟡 `Math.sqrt(area / r)` and `Math.sqrt(area * r)` compute width and height from the area, but after `Math.max` and `Math.round` are applied independently to each, the resulting aspect ratio may no longer match `r`, and the preserved area can drift significantly — especially when one dimension is clamped to `minimumWidth`/`minimumHeight`. Consider computing one dimension first (e.g., width), then deriving the other strictly from it:\n\n```suggestion\n            const newWidth \u003d Math.max(minimumWidth, Math.round(Math.sqrt(area / r)));\n            const newHeight \u003d Math.max(minimumHeight, Math.round(newWidth * r));\n```\n\nThis ensures the aspect ratio is actually honoured after clamping.",
      "revId": "b2c75e980a9cda3bc84af68e32b4c9299b4409d7",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
