      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 78: 🔴 Re-entrancy guard is ineffective. Setting `_resizing \u003d true`, then synchronously assigning `width` and `height`, then setting `_resizing \u003d false` assumes that `onWidthChanged` fires synchronously during the assignment. In Qt/QML, property-change signals on `Window.width`/`Window.height` can be deferred (especially on Wayland or when the window manager mediates the resize). If the signal fires asynchronously after `_resizing` has already been reset to `false`, the guard is bypassed and `_applyVideoAspect()` will recurse or produce incorrect geometry.\n\nConsider using a `Qt.callLater` pattern or a timer to coalesce the resize, or use a counter instead of a boolean:\n\n```suggestion\n            _resizing++;\n            width \u003d newWidth;\n            height \u003d newHeight;\n            _resizing--;\n```\n\nAnd change the guard check in `onWidthChanged` to `if (_resizing \u003d\u003d\u003d 0)`.\n\nHowever, even this won\u0027t help if the WM delivers the size change asynchronously. A more robust approach is to skip re-applying aspect when the current width/height already satisfy the target ratio within tolerance.",
      "revId": "b2c75e980a9cda3bc84af68e32b4c9299b4409d7",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
