      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 196: 🔴 `onWidthChanged` now calls both `_applyVideoAspect()` and `saveGeometry()` unconditionally (geometry is saved even during programmatic resizes). But `_applyVideoAspect()` itself changes `height`, which triggers `onHeightChanged` → `saveGeometry()` again. This means every aspect-ratio adjustment triggers `saveGeometry()` at least twice (once for width, once for height) with an intermediate, possibly incorrect geometry. If `saveGeometry()` persists to disk/settings, this can save a geometry where only width has been updated but height hasn\u0027t yet.\n\nConsider guarding `saveGeometry()` as well:\n\n```suggestion\n    onWidthChanged: { if (!_resizing) { _applyVideoAspect(); saveGeometry(); } }\n    onHeightChanged: { if (!_resizing) saveGeometry(); }\n```",
      "revId": "b2c75e980a9cda3bc84af68e32b4c9299b4409d7",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
