      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 63: 🟡 When `remoteVideo.isRendering` transitions from `true` to `false` (e.g., the remote camera is temporarily disabled), `videoInvAspectRatio` drops to `0`. This triggers `onVideoInvAspectRatioChanged` in the parent, but `_applyVideoAspect()` returns early because `r \u003c\u003d 0`. While not buggy, `_lastInvAspect` retains the stale value, so when video resumes at the *same* resolution, `r \u003d\u003d\u003d _lastInvAspect` and the code takes the \u0027user resize\u0027 path rather than the \u0027aspect changed\u0027 path. This is probably fine but worth a comment to make the intent clear.",
